{"TopicId":198900,"ForumId":25,"TopicTitle":"Rebuild the network","CreatedByName":"Mathrilord","CreatedById":56196,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-20T21:48:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Mathrilord","CreatedById":56196,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-20T21:48:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh no! A powerful Kerbol flare\u00A0knocked out all\u00A0communication systems.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYour mission:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nKerbin: Provide us the cheapest solution to rapidly rebuild the satellite network around Kerbin. (full-surface coverage)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRules:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0Stock, dlc allowed\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0Extra ground station disabled.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0Extra launch site disabled.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n\u00A0CommNet difficulty, to be talked about likely normal.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nAll kerbals must be brought back to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nTo reuse a part, it must be brought back to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nYour cost must represent the\u00A0full operation, you pay only once for something you use multiple time like a plane, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, recovered stage, etc\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat network configuration will you choose?\u003Cbr\u003E\nWill you launch your satellites one by one or all at once?\u003Cbr\u003E\nCheap srbs, multipurpose \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, reusable rockets?\u003Cbr\u003E\nMaybe a tug to move your satellites or a boat to recover your booster?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWIP\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI want your opinion to improve this challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-20T22:03:33Z\u0022 title=\u002212/20/2020 10:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Mathrilord\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"randomspacedude","CreatedById":207079,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-20T22:11:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSound interesting\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"chadgaskerman","CreatedById":155837,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-22T13:47:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would assume Stratolaunchers count as reusable, even if they are a kind of irrecoverable properly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mathrilord","CreatedById":56196,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-22T19:06:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155837-chadgaskerman/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155837\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155837-chadgaskerman/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@chadgaskerman\u003C/a\u003ESure stratolaunchers count as reusable but not its fuel to launch AND\u00A0land.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-22T19:06:49Z\u0022 title=\u002212/22/2020 07:06  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 22, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Mathrilord\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ffx","CreatedById":200313,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-11T02:48:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207079-randomspacedude/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022207079\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/207079-randomspacedude/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@randomspacedude\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0is your profile picture a cuttlefish?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jinnantonix","CreatedById":188889,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-12T04:21:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/56196-mathrilord/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002256196\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/56196-mathrilord/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mathrilord\u003C/a\u003Efor re-usability you may wish to the close the loophole on using ore and mining on the runway to avoid fuel costs.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAlso, full surface coverage may be debatable.\u00A0 I would argue that two relays directly opposite each other in equatorial orbit will give 100% coverage of Kerbin.\u00A0 Does coverage also include a relay capable of communicating with Eeloo?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"randomspacedude","CreatedById":207079,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-02-14T23:35:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223924129\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022198900\u0022 data-ipsquote